The following are major news items in leading Kenyan
newspapers Tuesday. Kenya Times: -- The Kenyan government has
intensified security patrols on its common border with Tanzania in
Loitokitok sub-District to stem the increased wave of crime in the
area, District Commissioner Charles Chemjor said. Daily Nation: -- A
high-level meeting of Ugandan and Sudanese officials is scheduled to
take place in the Kenyan capital Nairobi in January with a view to
exchanging diplomats, Ugandan officials said. East African Standard: --
Jean Bosco Ndayikengurukiye, head of Burundi's main rebel organization,
said he would not take part in multi-party peace talks under former
South African President Nelson Mandela, and instead asked for direct
talks with the government and army.
